# Constants templates (from `constants.json`)

Summarizes **102** files matched by **`**/constants/**`** or **`*.constant.ts`** (see [`.agents/file-lists/constants.json`](../file-lists/constants.json)). Keep constants separate from types and components (**`rules-typescript-clean-code.mdc`**).

## Inventory snapshot

| Fact | Typical value |
| --- | --- |
| Basename contains `.constant` | ~83% |
| Extensions | `.ts` mostly; some `.tsx`, `.scss`, `.js` |
| Path depth (median) | 7 segments |
| Common roots | `app/pages` (~52%), `app/features` (~21%), `app/constants` (~18%), `wireframe/configuration` (~8%) |

**Path examples:**

- `app/constants/PartnerId.constant.ts`
- `app/constants/DetailsPageUrlStorageKey.ts`
- `app/pages/Result/constants/Foo.constant.ts` (when feature-local)

## Patterns

### A — `*.constant.ts` (scalar or object config)

```typescript
export const PARTNER_ID = 24;
export const API_TIMEOUT_MS = 5000;
```

### B — Multiple related exports (storage keys, URLs)

```typescript
export const NOTES_STORAGE_KEY = "daily_magic_notes_draft";
export const THEME_STORAGE_KEY = "daily_magic_theme";
```

### C — `constants/` folder

- Group by domain; use **UPPER_SNAKE** for immutable primitives and key strings when they are true constants.

## Immutability

- Prefer **`export const`** and **readonly** shapes when exporting objects.
- Do not mutate imported constants.

## Related

- Enums: **`enums-templates.mdc`**
- Text keys: use **`TEXT_MANAGER`** / **`generate-texts`** per **`rules-bundle-core.mdc`** (do not hand-edit `TextManager.constant.ts`).
